The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, April 07, 2004 				 Reese shows Blonde can play ball, too
				 	 Sport struck: Reese Witherspoon																								Los Angeles, April 6 (Reuters): Actor Reese Witherspoon will star in and produce Sports Widow, a romantic comedy about a woman who one-ups her football-obsessed husband by becoming an expert on the sport.																								The Universal Pictures project will be directed by David Mirkin (Romy and Micheles High School Reunion), who will also rewrite Liz Kruger and Craig Shapiros script. 																								Witherspoon will produce the films under her Type A Films banner. 																								She was last in theatres with Legally Blonde 2.
